Cape Town – Police are investigating a case of murder after a 3-year old boy caught in alleged gang crossfire was killed in Rylands. Police spokesperson Captain FC van Wyk said the incident took place at around 10.15am on Monday at Pook se Bos informal settlement when unidentified men in a white vehicle opened fire in the direction of the address where the child was. No arrests had been made. "According to reports, a group of unidentified men driving a light delivery vehicle started to shoot towards the address where the child was. The child was caught in the crossfire and was shot in the head. "The injured child was taken to a nearby hospital for medical treatment and died later in hospital due to injuries sustained. The attempted murder case was changed to a murder." Arrangements have been made for counselling for the family, said Van Wyk. Cape Times